132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 189
H.P. 122 House of Representatives, January 14, 2025
An Act to Increase Availability and Affordability of Mental Health
Care and Substance Use Disorder Services by Removing the
Certificate of Need Requirement
Reference to the Committee on Health Coverage, Insurance and Financial Services
suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative LIBBY of Auburn.
Cosponsored by Senator BALDACCI of Penobscot and
Representatives: HASENFUS of Readfield, LAJOIE of Lewiston, MILLIKEN of Blue Hill,
SINCLAIR of Bath, SKOLD of Portland.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §330, sub-§6, as enacted by PL 2001, c. 664, §2, is amended to
3 read:
4 6. Existing capacity. The use by an ambulatory surgical facility licensed on January
5 1, 1998 of capacity in existence on January 1, 1998; and
6 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §330, sub-§7, as amended by PL 2003, c. 621, §1, is further
7 amended to read:
8 7. Critical access hospitals. Conversion by a critical access hospital or a hospital in
9 the process of becoming a critical access hospital of licensed acute care beds to hospital
10 swing beds.; and
11 Sec. 3. 22 MRSA §330, sub-§8 is enacted to read:
12 8. Mental health and substance use disorder services. Mental and behavioral health
13 care services and substance use disorder detoxification and treatment services offered by a
14 health care facility.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This bill eliminates the requirement for health care facilities to obtain a certificate of
1177 need for the provision of mental and behavioral health care services and substance use
1188 disorder detoxification and treatment services.
